    "text": "<p><i>Remove curse</i> can remove all curses on an object or a creature. If the target is a creature, you must make a caster level check (1d20 + caster level) against the DC of each curse affecting the target. Success means that the curse is removed. <i>Remove curse</i> does not remove the curse from a cursed shield, weapon, or suit of armor, although a successful caster level check enables the creature afflicted with any such cursed item to remove and get rid of it.</p><p><i>Remove curse</i> counters and dispels <i>bestow curse</i>.</p>", 
